* old page number $=$ new page number.
* Let old page number be a multiple of $10$ & Newton's lemma non multiple of $10$ be $z$.
* According to the question :*
\begin{align}
10a+z -(10b+z')&=10a+z - 10(b+1) +z'
\end{align}
* \implies a=b+1
\end{align}
$\mathbf{Therefore,}$ the $\mathbf{answer} \space$ \begin{align}
\mathbf{20}
\end{align}

